Ivory Coast Coffee-Bean Exports From Abidjan Fell 43% in August

-- B y   O l i v i e r   M o n n i e r
-- 
2011-10-04T16:00:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/ivory-coast-coffee-bean-exports-from-abidjan-fell-43-in-august.html
Exports of coffee beans from  Ivory
Coast â€™s port of Abidjan, the commercial capital, fell 43 percent
in August, according to data from the harbor.  Shipments amounted to 5,458 metric tons, compared with
9,515 tons in the same period a year earlier. Exports of soluble
coffee produced in  Abidjan  rose to 705 tons from 589 tons a year
ago in the same period.  Ivory Coast primarily grows robusta beans, a variety mainly
used in instant coffee and espresso.  To contact the reporters on this story:
